    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-23T23:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-23T23:09:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <head>105. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station</gloss> in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >place not declassified</hi>]<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d105fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79-01025A, Box 2, Folder 2.
                        Secret; Priority; <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>; RYBAT.
                        Repeated to the Director of Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-24T04:09:00+00:00">February 24, 1954,
                        0409Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>711. 1. HDQs considering pros and con of establishing covert official
                    relationship with [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] to ensure full
                    support <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> objectives.</p>
                <p>2. <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> desires your views soonest whether: <list>
                        <label>A.</label>
                        <item>High ranking <gloss target="#t_KUBARK1">KUBARK</gloss> official
                            necessary or</item>
                        <label>B.</label>
                        <item>Mature personable individual not necessarily top echelon;</item>
                        <pb facs="0233" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/>
                        <label>C.</label>
                        <item>Civilian or</item>
                        <label>D.</label>
                        <item>Military status;</item>
                        <label>E.</label>
                        <item>General approach adequate or</item>
                        <label>F.</label>
                        <item>Specific knowledgeable approach required.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>3. Appreciate your candid views receptivity [<hi rend="italic">name not
                        declassified</hi>] such proposition assuming properly laid on by HDQs.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
